A simple, fast Webkit web browser for GNOME.

== Installation ==

<code>emerge epiphany</code>

USE Flags:

<b>avahi</b> -- Add avahi/Zeroconf support<br>
<b>debug</b> -- Enable extra debug codepaths, like asserts and extra output. If you want to get meaningful backtraces see http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/qa/backtraces.xml<br>
<b>doc</b> -- Enable documentation.<br>
<b>introspection</b> -- Use gobject-introspection for introspection<br>
<b>networkmanager</b> -- Enable networkmanager support.<br>
<b>nss</b> -- Import passwords from older gecko-based epiphany keyring.

== Flash support ==

In order to get flash support: <code>emerge adobe-flash</code>.  And then, <code>emerge nspluginwrapper</code>.  
 
Execute the following command to get flash working in Epiphany (on 32 bit): <code>/usr/lib/nspluginwrapper/i386/linux/npconfig -v -a -n -i</code>.  

For 64 bit, change i386 in the previous command to x86_64.
